 for visiting family, friends or relatives in Sri Lanka.\r\nSri Lanka Business Visa - Issued for the purpose of undertaking business activities in Sri Lanka such as attending meetings, conferences, seminar or training.\r\nSri Lanka Transit Visa - Issued if you are transiting to a third country via Sri Lanka.\";}', 'a:1:{i:0;s:450:\"Step 1:Provide your travel details to our Sri Lanka Visa Expert and get all your queries answered.\r\n<br>\r\nStep 2: Pay your Sri Lanka visa cost online and upload all your documents online through our secured online document locker to ensure its confidentiality.\r\n<br>\r\nStep 3: Our Visa Experts will thoroughly verify and scrutinize your documents and further submit it online.\r\n<br>\r\nStep 4: Receive your Sri Lanka Visa online, directly in your Inbox.\";}', 'a:1:{i:0;s:495:\"Have a valid Passport and valid SriLankaTourist Visa<br>\r\nHave sufficient funds to support yourself and all family members during your entire trip.<br>\r\nThorough knowledge of your accommodation and itinerary details to furnish at immigration if asked to<br>\r\nReturn or onward flight tickets to ensure return to your home country or your next destination once the Dubai visa for Indians expires<br>\r\nAdhere to the moral standards of the country and follow the general rules<br>\r\nBe in good health\";}', 'a:1:{i:0;s:73:\"Passport; <br>\r\nValid Sri Lanka Visa; <br>\r\nConfirmed return Ticket; <br>\";}', 'a:1:{i:0;s:504:\"Keep all your travel documents ready to be produced for verification by the immigration officers <br>\r\nEnsure you are not carrying any forbidden items that will not pass through customs, including ‚Äòany immoral items liable to cause a breach of the peace‚Äô like books, audiobooks, audio and video tapes <br>\r\nAlways carry your passport or a copy of it while traveling within Dubai <br>\r\nNote down emergency helpline numbers in the country <br>\r\nBe aware of the general rules of conduct in public places\";}', 'a:1:{i:0;s:3522:\"A tiny island country that delights with a huge tourism bouquet. A Sri Lankan holiday spoils you with choice ‚Äì beaches, hill stations, world heritage sites, wildlife and tea plantations, all come together to fill your vacation itinerary with options.\r\nLocals usually speak in Tamil and Sinhala, though a huge chunk speaks in English as well. This further boosts tourism, given that the average tourist from around the world is attracted to tropical beaches. A typical trip to Sri Lanka should take you to a beach or two, up into a misty hill station, see you spend time with elephants and whales, or explore ancient world heritage sites. Placed near the equator, Sri Lanka enjoys consistently tropical weather. Different parts of the country can be visited at different times during the year, making it tourist friendly most of the time. Visitors head to its beaches, hill stations, tea plantations and wildlife centres throughout the year. Sri Lanka, being an island nation peppered with beaches and ancient sites, remains a popular choice with travellers following different itineraries. Beach bums, adventure seekers, trekkers, and culture vultures all head to the country for their idea of a good time. Like all tourist friendly destinations, Sri Lanka has accommodation and food options for all budgets ‚Äì from the basic to the average, and all the way to the luxurious.\r\nSri Lanka is the land of nature and wildlife. The tiny island is every beach lover‚Äôs paradise. With its mesmerising beaches and magical landscapes, Sri Lanka is truly a gem. It is one of the hottest and popular weekend getaways for many. Rich in culture, heritage, history and natural beauty, Sri Lanka is truly alluring. With sun-kissed beaches, historical ruins, affordable prices, elephants, tea and some lip-smacking cuisine make Sri Lanka undeniably awesome. Sri Lanka is a rich and fascinating country that seems to have everything a traveller could possibly desire. The country is one of the best safari destinations outside of Africa with an abundance of wildlife squeezed into its 26 national parks. There are verdant rainforests, misty hills amid fertile tea plantations and miles upon miles of dazzling beaches. You‚Äôve got a perfect holiday destination squeezed into an island a quarter of the size of the UK!\r\n\r\nThe ideal way to move within the country is by trains and Tuk-Tuk. Tuk-Tuk is quite cheap as you have to pay approximately $20 for a whole day visit. Various typical routes to travel by Tuk-Tuk are Galle to Colombo that costs $2, Kandy to Nuwara is around $2, and Jaffna to Colombo is about $3.\r\n\r\nWhat‚Äôs more, the country is affordable and full of delicious cuisine as well as intriguing history. The people have dealt with war, disaster and all the challenges of a developing south-Asian country ‚Äì and they have done it with grace and humility. Despite the nation‚Äôs recent turmoil, the country and its people are moving quickly forward.\r\n\r\nGetting a Sri Lankan visa for Indian tourists requires you to apply for an online Sri Lanka Visa before travelling. An ETA, or an Electronic Travel Authorisation (Sri Lanka e visa), allows Indian tourists to stay in Sri Lanka for up to 30 days. This time period can be extended for up to 6 months. So whether it is a vacation to the beach you are in the mood for, a quiet trip to a quaint, colonial hill station, or connecting with wildlife, Sri Lanka has a destination that suits all travel itineraries. Apply online for Srilanka e visa, get packed, and off you go!\";}', 'a:1:{i:0;s:820:\"Sri Lanka Visa requirements not met <br> The most common reason for rejection of e visa for Sri Lanka from India is if the Sri Lankan Immigration authorities‚Äôs visa requirements have not been met. For instance: Invalid or damaged passport, less pages in passport etc. When considering an application for a Srilanka visit visa, the Sri Lanka High Commission is looking to assess whether the applicant meets the eligibility and suitability requirements to enter Sri Lanka. Failing to demonstrate that you meet the requirements will get your application rejected. <br> Wrong Visa type applied <br> For example, if you are travelling to Sri Lanka to attend a meeting or seminar, you would not be eligible to travel on a Srilanka visit visa or tourist visa and would instead need to apply for the appropriate business visa.\";}', 'a:1:{i:0;s:1302:\"Visa application fees along with the service charge are non-refundable in all cases. Even in case of visa application rejection the entire amount is non-refundable. <br>\r\nVisa application approval/rejection and processing time is at the sole discretion of the immigration and we do not have any control over the same. <br>\r\nVisa applications may require more than usual working days for processing and it is completely dependent on the immigration. <br>\r\nImmigration/Ykstrip.in may ask for additional documents on a case to case basis. <br>\r\nPrices are correct at the time of publication and are subject to change without notice. <br>\r\nVisa applications processing will only be after the verification of all required documents and receipt of complete payment. <br>\r\nVisas issued under visit/business/transit/tourist profession are not eligible to work in the destination country. <br>\r\nYkstrip.in reserves the right to refuse applications at its discretion and bears no liability for the processing time or rejection of visa applications by the immigration. <br>\r\nTraveller or the customer has to fully bear the penalty amount in case the destination country levy any charges. <br>\r\nAdditional charges such as documents courier, photograph development, attestation etc has to be borne by the applicant.\";}');

